","sectionId":"environment","webTitle":"Electrosmog: the environmental threat that Noel Edmonds wants to save us from","references":[],"webPublicationDate":"2015-08-05T13:40:38Z","fields":{"shouldHideAdverts":"false","wordcount":"356","shortUrl":"http://gu.com/p/4b9t2","secureThumbnail":"https://static-secure.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2015/8/5/1438774473990/5cc08d76-794f-4bea-9592-6efbcb9597dd-140x84.jpeg","main":"<figure class=\"element element-image\" data-media-id=\"756bfc6811fbd9635f26a50f66d1e8d2db71d08d\"> <img src=\"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2015/8/5/1438774473615/5cc08d76-794f-4bea-9592-6efbcb9597dd-460x276.jpeg\" alt=\"Noel Edmonds electrosmog\" width=\"460\" height=\"276\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption> <span class=\"element-image__caption\">Noel Edmonds: on the lookout for electrosmog. </span> <span class=\"element-image__credit\">Photograph: Karen Robinson</span> </figcaption> </figure>","liveBloggingNow":"false","body":"<p><strong>Name: </strong>Electrosmog.<br /></p> <p><strong>Age:</strong> As old as electromagnetism itself.</p> <p><strong>Appearance:</strong> As bad as Ebola, climate change and Aids combined reckons Noel Edmonds, but worse because it’s invisible, or something.</p> <p><strong>Or something? That doesn’t sound very authoritative.</strong> Well, you try summing up the greatest single threat facing mankind in a pithy sentence.</p> <p><strong>Listen, I don’t even know what electrosmog is, but I’m pretty sure it isn’t the greatest threat facing mankind.</strong> It is.</p> <p><strong>Who says?</strong> I told you: Noel Edmonds.</p> <p><strong>Noel Edmonds?</strong> In an <a href=\"http://www.mirror.co.uk/3am/celebrity-news/noel-edmonds-death-doesnt-exist-6194153\">interview with the Daily Mirror</a>, Edmonds claimed that electrosmog – clouds of electromagnetic fields caused by Wi-Fi, phone signals and electricity – is endangering humanity. It’s making us electrosensitive, and systematically destroying our own natural electromagnetic fields.</p> <p><strong>And that’s a bad thing because?</strong> “All you are is energy, remember that.” There, a direct Edmonds quote. </p> <p><strong>Interesting. Got any more?</strong> He also said: “There isn’t such a thing as death, it’s just departure. You cannot die. It’s been known for a very long time.”</p> <p><strong>Riiiiiiiight. </strong>No, it’s worth listening to. Edmonds is an expert at this stuff. Remember when <a href=\"http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/health/alternative-medicine/3338065/Need-a-lover-or-a-house-Call-on-the-cosmos.html\">he discovered cosmic ordering</a> almost a decade ago? He sent a message out to the universe and, as a result, <a href=\"http://www.religionnewsblog.com/14246/dear-cosmos-can-i-have-a-hit-show\">his career was instantly rehabilitated</a>.</p> <p><strong>Yes, he got to present a ridiculous quasi-superstitious </strong><strong><a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/media/2006/oct/21/broadcasting.arts\">daytime quiz show</a></strong><strong> where contestants are financially rewarded by actively denying the concept of coincidence.</strong> Look, it’s a job.</p> <p><strong>Anyway, how worried should I be about electrosmog? </strong>Really worried. Oh, sure, 10 years ago the World Health Organisation <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/technology/2007/jan/18/guardianweeklytechnologysection4\">denied that electromagnetic fields had any negative effect</a> on humans, stating: “There is no scientific basis to link ES [electrosensitive] symptoms to EMF exposure.” But then it would say that, wouldn’t it?</p> <p><strong>Would it?</strong> Of course it would. This is a huge conspiracy. A huge global conspiracy, and all the corporations are in on it. They want to enslave us all with magnets. Edmonds is right. He’s like our Jesus.</p> <p><strong>Which makes Mr Blobby?</strong> I dunno, Moses or something.</p> <p><strong>Do say:</strong> “Let’s stop the scourge of electrosmog by banning Wi-Fi.”</p> <p><strong>Don’t say:</strong> “Let’s also stop it by unplugging our TVs whenever we see Noel Edmonds.”</p>","internalOctopusCode":"10650803","productionOffice":"UK","newspaperEditionDate":"2015-08-06T00:00:00Z","hasStoryPackage":"false","internalPageCode":"2349326","internalContentCode":"457667842","publication":"The Guardian","trailText":"The Deal Or No Deal presenter has warned of mankind’s greatest danger, but it’s OK as ‘there isn’t such a thing as death’","allowUgc":"false","headline":"Electrosmog: the environmental threat that Noel Edmonds wants to save us from","isInappropriateForSponsorship":"false","commentable":"true","firstPublicationDate":"2015-08-05T14:40:38.843+01:00","thumbnail":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2015/8/5/1438774473990/5cc08d76-794f-4bea-9592-6efbcb9597dd-140x84.jpeg","isPremoderated":"false","internalComposerCode":"55c1f23fe4b0528dcd379c7b","newspaperPageNumber":"3","commentCloseDate":"2015-08-08T14:45:00+01:00","standfirst":"<p>The Deal Or No Deal presenter has warned of mankind’s greatest danger, but it’s OK as ‘there isn’t such a thing as death’</p>","linkText":"Electrosmog: the environmental threat that Noel Edmonds wants to save us from","showInRelatedContent":"true","lastModified":"2015-08-06T17:33:42.000+01:00"},"webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/environment/shortcuts/2015/aug/05/electrosmog-the-environmental-threat-that-noel-edmonds-wants-to-save-us-from","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/environment/shortcuts/2015/aug/05/electrosmog-the-environmental-threat-that-noel-edmonds-wants-to-save-us-from","sectionName":"Environment","tags":[{"id":"environment/environment","webTitle":"Environment","type":"keyword","sectionId":"environment","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/environment/environment","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/environment/environment","sectionName":"Environment","references":[]},{"id":"news/series/pass-notes","webTitle":"Pass notes","description":"A quick c